info.title: Selling Partner API for Amazon External Fulfillment Shipments Processing
info.description: This section provides APIs for selling partners to work with Amazon External Fulfillment shipments management/processing services.

get.description: An API for a client to retrieve an optional list of shippingOptions that marketplace/channel provides for the pickup of the packages of an shipment. This API will return a list of shippingOptions if the marketplace/channel provides transportation and allows the seller to choose a shippingOption. If the marketplace/channel does not allow for a shippingOption to be selected, but has a pre-determined shippingOption, then this API will return an empty response.

SerialNumber.description: The hsn code of SKU in this lineItem.

trackingId.description: The tracking number of the package.

pickupWindow.description: The time window between which the package was picked up.

ShipLabelMetadata.description: Contains Metadata about the ship label document.

metadata.description: Contains Metadata about the ship label document.

channelLocationId.description: The location identifier of Seller's location in marketplace channel to which shipment has been dropped for fulfillment.

charges.description: The charges associated with the shipment. The charge amount does not include the tax amount.

lastUpdatedDateTime.description: The date/time at which the shipment was last updated.

referenceId.description: A unique identifier for every shipment rejection raised by the caller.

lineItems.description: Details about the line items from the shipment that are being confirmed/rejected by the seller.

ShipmentAcknowledgementRequest.description: The request schema for the confirm/reject shipment line items.

ShipmentAcknowledgementRequest_lineItem.description: Contains information about the line item being confirmed/rejected.

reason.description: The reason for the rejection of line item incase it is being rejected.

id.description: An identifier for a shipment's line item. This identifier is guaranteed to be unique within the scope of its containing shipment.

merchantSku.description: The seller's identifier for the SKU in this line item.

numberOfUnits.description: The number of items of the SKU of this line item.

serialNumberRequired.description: Indicates if serial numbers need to be provided for this line item.

serialNumbers.description: The serial number(s) for each item in this line item.

hazmatLabelsRequired.description: Indicatets if hazardous material labels need to be applied on packages containing this line item or not.

hazmatLabels.description: A list of Hazmat label identifiers that are to be applied on the packages for this line item.

charges.description: The charges associated with the line item. The charge amount does not include the tax amount.

cancellations.description:
A list of cancellations for the given line item. This allows for partial cancellation of an shipment's line item.
Supported CancellationType:

* **SELLER_REJECTED:** Cancellation initiated by seller.

* **MARKETPLACE_CANCELLATION:** Cancellation initiated by marketplace.

* **SYSTEM_CANCELLED:** Cancellation initiated by Yojaka. No further action is needed.

**NOTE:** Currently, Amazon Yojaka does not support partial cancellation of an shipment or its line items.
This list will contain a single value with all the cancellation details.

ShipmentLineItem.description: Contains information about one line item in a shipment.

cancelledQuantity.description: The quantity of items of this particular item which have been cancelled.

cancelledTimestamp.description: The number of milliseconds since epoch in UTC when the line item was cancelled.

cancellationType.description: The type of cancellation of the item in the shipment.

cancellationReason.description: The reason for the cancellation of the shipment

ShipmentLineItem_cancellations.description: Represents an shipment item's cancellation details.

giftWrapRequired.description: A boolean value indicating if the line item is to be gift wrapped or not.

giftWrapLabel.description: The label to be printed on the wrapped gift.

giftMessagePresent.description: Indicates if there is a gift message that has to be printed on the wrapped gift.

giftMessage.description: The gift message that is to be printed on the wrapped gift.

ShipmentLineItem_giftAttributes.description: Contains information about any gift wrapping that is needed for this line item.

shipmentType.description:
Contains the shipment type.
* "REPLACEMENT" when replacing shipment's SKUs are same as the original shipment
* "EXCHANGE" when replacing shipment's SKUs are different from original shipment.
* "NEW" when it's a new shipment.

numberOfUnits.description: Total number of units in the shipment.

priority.description: Indicates if the shipment is an Amazon Prime shipment or not.

id.description: The unique id of the adapter

name.description: The unique name of the adapter

id.description: The unique id of the invoice corresponding to this shipment.

creationDateTime.description: The time of creation of invoice

Shipment_metadata_invoiceInformation.description: Invoice related information for the shipment.

channelName.description: The name of marketplace channel from which shipment has been dropped for fulfillment.

channelLocationId.description: The location identifier of Seller's location in marketplace channel to which shipment has been dropped for fulfillment.

originalLineItems.description: The line items from original shipment corresponding to this shipment

Shipment_metadata_originalShipmentInfo.description: This field contains the details of the original shipment, if the ShipmentType is either "REPLACEMENT" or "EXCHANGE".

originalSku.description: SKU id for the original shipment

charges.description: The charge details at shipment level.

recommendedShipMethod.description: The ship method assigned by Amazon Fulfillment Network for the packages in this shipment.

expectedShippingDateTime.description: The date/time at which Amazon expects the seller to ship the packages in this shipment.

shipToAddress.description: The address to which the packages are to be shipped to. Only basic information about the buyer's address needed for taxation purposes are provided here.

shippingType.description: The type of shipping that seller will use to deliver a customer order.

recommendedPackages.description: Recommendations for packages in an order.

Shipment_shippingInfo.description: Contains shipping information for the the packages for this shipment.

shipments.description: The list of shipments in the response.

pagination.description: Indicates if one or more pages of shipments are available.

ShipmentsResponse.description: The response schema for the getShipments operation.

shippingOptionId.description: An identifier for the offering provided by service.

pickupWindow.description: The time window between which the package will be picked up.

ShippingOptions.description: Shipping Response entity for a single package

shippingOptions.description: The list of shipping options in the response.

ShippingOptionsResponse.description: The response entity returned to the client by the retrieve pickup shippingOptions API. The response contains 0 or more shippingOptions on a per-package basis from which the seller has to select one shippingOption while retrieving the ship-label. If the particular marketplace/channel does not support scheduled shippingOption, then this response will be empty.

TimeWindow.description: Time duration used to specify the interval of an event. Eg: PickUp, Delivery.

trackingId.description: The tracking number of the package.

TrackingDetails.description: Contains tracking detilas about the shipping.

value.description: The numerical value of the weight. Must be a positive value.

weightUnit.description: The unit of measurement of the weight.

Weight.description: Represents the weight of a package.
